<br>
Well, Quinloe, son, considering that in almost every game (with the lone exception being the bar game &quot;Spam&quot;, for those of you familiar) there are rules, you have to agree to the rules before you can even start the software, there's a provision in the rules which say the operators can kick you out if you break the rules (actually for any reason at all, but arbitrarily kicking people out isn't good for business, it's more of a 'cover our ass' provision), the vast majority of players adhere to the ruleset, and macros offer a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>tremendous</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> advantage over said players, yes, I'd say it's cheating.<br>
<br>
Even in games you pay for. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A> at: 6/20/03 9:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1367<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 5:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hacking</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Well, Quinloe, son, considering that in almost every game (with the lone exception being the bar game &quot;Spam&quot;, for those of you familiar) there are rules, you have to agree to the rules before you can even start the software, there's a provision in the rules which say the operators can kick you out if you break the rules (actually for any reason at all, but arbitrarily kicking people out isn't good for business, it's more of a 'cover our ass' provision), the vast majority of players adhere to the ruleset, and macros offer a tremendous advantage over said players, yes, I'd say it's cheating.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
